A Sudanese sleuth yesterday appeared in court following the disappearance of two Sudan nationals under mysterious circumstances in Nairobi.The court had issued a warrant of arrest against John Toplam after the families of Dong Luak and Aggrey Izbon said he called them, seeking to know the details of an affidavit filed in the case. Luak and Izbon worked for the Sudan People&rsquo;s Liberation Movement in opposition. They disappeared on January 23.Toplam was released on a personal bond of Sh10,000. The case will be mentioned on February 9.